# Copy to .dev.vars for local Pages Functions secrets (not committed).
# wrangler pages dev loads .dev.vars automatically.
#
# Workers Builds / CI: set CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN in the Cloudflare project (not in this file).
# See docs/CLOUDFLARE_WORKERS_BUILDS.md — token needs Account → Cloudflare Pages → Edit.
#
# UAT / local API: run `npm run db:migrate:local` once, then `npm run pages:dev`
# (Vite on 8080 proxies /api to wrangler on 8788 — see vite.config.ts).
#
# Optional — Cloudflare Access JWT enforcement on /api/* (omit for local open APIs):
# ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=https://yourteam.cloudflareaccess.com
# ACCESS_POLICY_AUD=<application_audience_tag_from_zero_trust>
#
# App login (username/password) — HS256 secret for session cookie + Bearer JWT; enables /api protection when set:
# AUTH_JWT_SECRET=generate-a-long-random-string
#
# EXAMPLE_SECRET=dev-only-value

# Phase 8 production hardening — set these in the CF Pages dashboard for production.
# Each integration is a NO-OP without its credential; setting the var activates it.
# See docs/PRODUCTION-RUNBOOK.md for the operational playbook.
#
# Stripe webhook signing secret (starts with `whsec_…`, copy from Stripe → Webhooks → endpoint detail).
# When unset, POST /api/webhooks/stripe responds 503 stripe_not_configured.
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
#
# Server-side Sentry DSN. When unset, captureError() logs to console.
# SENTRY_DSN=
#
# R2 bucket name for D1 SQL dumps from scripts/backup-d1-to-r2.mjs. Falls back to
# MEDIA_BUCKET name from wrangler.toml with a warning if unset.
# BACKUP_BUCKET=

# --- Railway migration (Wave RM-α onwards) ---
# Postgres connection string for the Next.js / Drizzle path. Cloudflare Pages
# Functions ignore this; it is read by src/db/client.ts on the Node side.
# Defaults match docker-compose.dev.yml for local dev. See docs/RAILWAY-KICKOFF.md.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://sonic:sonic@localhost:5432/sonic_bloom_dev
